---
Source:
  - Title: Treasury of Traditional Wisdom
    Page: 322
  - Title: Râmôpanisad
Tags:
  - Combat-Action=Symbolism=The Worship of Images
---
It is for the advantage (artha) of the worshippers (upâsaka) (and not
by any intrinsic necessity) that Brahman -- whose nature is
intelligence (cin-maya), beside whom there is no other, who is
impartite and incorporeal—is aspectually conceived (rûpa-kalpanâ).
